{{for|similarly-named agencies in other jurisdictions|AAIB (disambiguation){{!}}AAIB}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}} {{Use British English|date=September 2016}}
'''Aircraft Accident Investigation Bureau''' (AAIB, {{lang-de|Büro für Flugunfalluntersuchungen}}, BFU; {{lang-fr|Bureau d'enquête sur les accidents d'aviation}}, BEAA; {{lang-it|Ufficio d'inchiesta sugli infortuni aeronautici}}, UIIA) was the [[Switzerland|Swiss]] bureau of aircraft accident investigation. In 2011, it was replaced by the [[Swiss Transportation Safety Investigation Board]].
==History== The Aircraft Accident Investigation Bureau was established by the [[Swiss parliament]]. Operations began in 1960.<ref>"[http://www.bfu.admin.ch/en/index.htm Welcome to the website of the Aircraft Accident Investigation Bureau]." ([https://www.webcitation.org/6GGE6rgtc?url=http://www.bfu.admin.ch/en/index.htm Archive]) Aircraft Accident Investigation Bureau. Retrieved on 30 April 2013.</ref> The bureau was headquartered on the grounds of [[Payerne Airport]] and in [[Payerne]].<ref>"[http://www.bfu.admin.ch/en/bfu_lageplan.htm How to find us] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100724115331/http://www.bfu.admin.ch/en/bfu_lageplan.htm |date=24 July 2010 }}." ([http://www.bfu.admin.ch/images/Anreise_BFU.jpg Map link] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110706221540/http://www.bfu.admin.ch/images/Anreise_BFU.jpg |date=6 July 2011 }}) Aircraft Accident Investigation Bureau. Retrieved on 9 June 2009. "Aircraft Accident Investigation Bureau AAIB Aeropole 1 Route de Morens 1530 Payerne Switzerland "</ref>
Normally the original aircraft accident reports were written in the language of the Swiss region where the aircraft accident occurred. Some reports had English versions available.<ref>"[http://www.bfu.admin.ch/en/dokumentation_berichte.htm Reports]." ([https://www.webcitation.org/6AU6ALBoR?url=http://www.bfu.admin.ch/en/dokumentation_berichte.htm Archive]) Aircraft Accident Investigation Bureau. Retrieved on 6 September 2012.</ref><!--If you are citing this page on other Wikipedias, keep in mind only the English version of the page says that some material will be in English and that the report titles indicate which languages are available!!!!-->
The agency was disestablished on 1 November 2011 when it and the [[Investigation Bureau for Railway, Funicular and Boat Accidents]] merged to form the [[Swiss Accident Investigation Board]].<ref>"[http://www.uvek.admin.ch/org/00469/02946/02958/index.html?lang=en Swiss Accident Investigation Board SAIB]." ([https://www.webcitation.org/6GGCyjF5x?url=http://www.uvek.admin.ch/org/00469/02946/02958/index.html?lang%3Den Archive]) [[Federal Department of the Environment, Transport, Energy and Communications]]. Retrieved on 30 April 2013.</ref>
==See also== *[[Crossair Flight 498]] *[[Crossair Flight 3597]] * [[Investigation Bureau for Railway, Funicular and Boat Accidents]]
