'''Bettembourg communal council''' ({{lang-fr|Conseil communal de Bettembourg}}) is the [[Local government|local council]] for the [[Communes of Luxembourg|commune]] of [[Bettembourg]], in southern [[Luxembourg]].
It consists of thirteen members, elected every six years by [[proportional representation]].<ref name="Conseil communal">{{cite web |url=http://www.bettembourg.lu/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=24&Itemid=185 |title=Le conseil communal |accessdate=2007-09-16 |date= |publisher=Commune of Bettembourg |language=fr}}</ref><ref name="Conseil échevinal">{{cite web |url=http://www.bettembourg.lu/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=23&Itemid=184 |title=Le conseil échevinal |accessdate=2007-09-16 |date= |publisher=Commune of Bettembourg |language=fr}}</ref> The last elections were held on 9 October 2005, and resulted in a victory for the [[Luxembourg Socialist Workers' Party]] (LSAP). In the ''[[Collège échevinal (Luxembourg)|collège échevinal]]'', the LSAP rules outright, under the leadership of [[Mayor of Bettembourg|mayor]] [[Roby Biwer]].<ref name="Conseil échevinal" />
