{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}} {{Use British English|date=December 2016}} {{Infobox street | name = Europa Road | native_name = | marker_image = | image = Europa Road, Gibraltar.jpg | caption = Southernmost section of Europa Road looking northwest. | former_names = | postal_code = | addresses = | length_m = | length_ft = | length_mi = | length_km = 2.9 | length_ref = | width = | location =[[Gibraltar]] | client = | maint = | coordinates = {{coord|36.126872|-5.349739|region:GI_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | direction_a = | terminus_a = | direction_b = | terminus_b = | junction = | commissioning_date = | construction_start_date = | completion_date = | inauguration_date = <!-- {{Start date|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | demolition_date = | north = | south = | east = | west = }} [[File:Europa Main Road, Alameda Gardens.jpg|thumb|250px|Old postcard depicting the section of Europa Road, between [[The Rock Hotel]] and [[Gibraltar Botanic Gardens]].]] '''Europa Road''' is a major [[road]] in the [[British Overseas Territories|British Overseas Territory]] of [[Gibraltar]]. It begins near [[Trafalgar Cemetery]] and [[Trafalgar Road, Gibraltar|Trafalgar Road]] and connects the centre with the southern tip of the territory at [[Europa Point]]. Along its way the road passes [[The Rock Hotel]], [[Gibraltar Botanic Gardens]], and the [[Ibrahim-al-Ibrahim Mosque]].<ref name="Tsouras2006">{{cite book|last=Tsouras|first=Peter|title=Hitler Triumphant: Alternate Decisions of World War II|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=TkuBnwqPoSsC&pg=PA82|accessdate=23 September 2012|date=29 September 2006|publisher=MBI Publishing Company|isbn=978-1-85367-699-4|page=82}}</ref>
