{{Infobox governor |name = Rodrigo Afonso |image = |caption = |background = |birth_name = |nationality = Portuguese |office=[[List of colonial governors of Cape Verde|Captain of Santiago, Cape Verde]] |term_start=1475 |term_end=1505 |predecessor=[[Diogo Afonso]] |successor=none, continued as colonial governor of Cape Verde |office2=[[List of colonial governors of Cape Verde|Captain of Boa Vista, Cape Verde]] |term_start2=1475 |term_end2=1505 |successor2=[[Pêro Correia]] }} '''Rodrigo Afonso''' ([[floruit|fl.]] late 15th century) was a Portuguese colonial administrator.
==Biography== His early life is unknown. He was probably born on Ribeira Grande (now [[Cidade Velha]]) and was the first colonial governor who was born in Cape Verde.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rulers.org/rulc1.html#Cabo_Verde|title=Cape Verde|website=rulers.org}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldstatesmen.org/Cape_Verde.html|title=Cape Verde|website=worldstatesmen.org}}</ref> He was probably was one of the first Portuguese people born in Cape Verde. He was likely a son of the explorer [[Diogo Afonso]].
He was later the 2nd and last captain of Northern [[Santiago, Cape Verde|Santiago]]. He was donated the island of [[Boa Vista, Cape Verde|Boa Vista]] in 1490 and became captain on from October 29, 1497 until 1505 and three days later for Boa Vista Island. The main administration of Southern Santiago would be ruled only by the [[List of colonial governors of Cape Verde|corregedor of Cape Verde]], from 1588 to 1975 as governor.
==See also== *[[List of colonial governors of Cape Verde]], including its predecessor the Captains of Northern Santiago and Boa Vista
