{{Infobox film | name = Sibi, l’âme du violon | image = | alt = <!-- see WP:ALT --> | caption = | director = Michel K. Zongo | producer = [[Berni Goldblat]] | writer = | screenplay = | story = | starring = | music = Sibi Zongo | cinematography = Michel K. Zongo | editing = [[Berni Goldblat]] | studio = | distributor = | released = {{Film date|2010}}<!-- {{Film date|Year|Month|Day|Location}} --> | runtime = 38 minutes | country = Burkina Faso | language = | budget = | gross = }}
'''''Sibi, l’âme du violon''''' is a 2010 documentary film directed by Michel K. Zongo.
== Synopsis == A blind violinist called Sibi has been singing and playing in cabarets in the most popular neighborhoods of [[Koudougou]], [[Burkina Faso]], for more than 30 years. He knows the origins of the ethnic groups and the most important family lines in the region. The film goes to the encounter of this extraordinary man who holds, despite himself and surrounded by general indifference, the living history of the region, and its oral traditions, now threatened with extinction. A message in a bottle before it is too late and these memories disappear forever.
